Prep the ingredients: Preheat the #oven{} to 400 degrees. In a small #pot{}, bring the @chicken stock concentrate{4} and @water{8%cups} to a simmer over low heat. Halve, peel, and finely dice the @yellow onion{1}(halved, peeled, and finely diced). Cut the @zucchini{16%oz} into ½-inch cubes. Mince or grate the @garlic{4%cloves}(minced). Zest and halve the @lemon{1}(zested and halved).

Roast the zucchini: Toss the zucchini on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Place in the oven for about ~{20%minutes}, tossing halfway through cooking, until golden brown.

Start the risotto: Meanwhile, heat @butter{2%tbsp} in a large #pan{} over medium heat. Add the onion and garlic and cook, tossing, for ~{5-6%minutes}, until softened. Season with salt and pepper. Add the @Arborio rice{1.5%cups} to the pan and cook, tossing, for another ~{1-2%minutes}, until translucent. Add the entire bunch of @thyme{1/4%oz} to the pan.

Begin adding the stock to the pan, ¼ cup at a time, until absorbed, stirring after each addition. Continue until the rice is al dente, for ~{25-30%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. The sauce should be thick but fairly loose. Discard the thyme stems.

> Some of the thyme leaves should fall off into the risotto while it infuses.

Finish the risotto: Once the risotto is al dente, stir in the @shrimp{20%oz} and @Parmesan cheese{2%oz}. Stir for ~{1-2%minutes}, until the shrimp are opaque. Stir in 1 teaspoon lemon zest and a squeeze of lemon. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Plate: Serve the risotto topped with a mound of zucchini and enjoy!